tSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Comparative law; European Private Law; Introduction; European Contract Law; Transnational Litigation. Optionals: European Company Law; European Consumer Law; European Family Law; European Tort Law; European State Aid; Law of the Economic and Monetary Union; European Integration.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>curriculum</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Lectures and seminars.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>instruction modes</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>tuition fee</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[This programme contributes to the enhancement of strategic cooperation and partnerships on the basis of teh core values of teh European Union: human rights, democracy and the rule of law.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>socio-economic contribution</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[This programme contributes to the enhancement of strategic cooperation and partnerships on the basis of teh core values of teh European Union: human rights, democracy and the rule of law.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>sustainable strengthening</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[A wide range of careers are open to graduates of this Master's programme. For those who have obtained a Bachelor's in Law at the UvA, the completion of the programme results in 'civil effect' in the Netherlands, meaning it gives access to the Dutch bar and magistracy. 

Finally, the Master's degree forms an excellent basis for an academic career in international or European law.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[The programme consists of two components, international law and European law, which share a number of mandatory courses. There are also a number of optional courses. This structure allows for specialisation in either of the components, while taking into account their common foundation. The programme seeks to develop an understanding of the theory and practice of international and European law.The teaching methods and evaluations focus on developing writing, analytical and communicative skills, as well as knowledge of Black Letter Law. To this end greater emphasis is placed on written and oral assignments than of traditional exams. 

The teaching staff includes highly qualified international and European lawyers. Students are exposed to a wide range of international institutions and assisted in pursuing internships and other career opportunities during and after completion of the programme. The LLM programme in International and European Law offers four tracks:

- European Union Law 
- European Competition Law and Regulation 
- International Trade and Investment Law 
- Public International Law]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The programme consists of two components, international law and European law, which share a number of mandatory courses. There are also a number of optional courses. This structure allows for specialisation in either of the components, while taking into account their common foundation. The programme seeks to provide students with an understanding of the theory and practice of international and European law.

The teaching methods and evaluations focus on developing writing, analytical and communication skills, as well as knowledge of Black Letter Law. To this end, a greater emphasis is placed on written and oral assignments than on traditional exams.

The teaching staff includes highly qualified international and European lawyers. Students are exposed to a wide range of international institutions and assisted in pursuing internships and other career opportunities during and after completion of the programme.

The LLM programme in International and European Law offers four tracks:

European Union Law 
European Union Business Law 
International Trade and Investment Law 
Public International Law]]></programDescription><programName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[International and European Law]]></programName><programName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[International and European Law]]></programName><programSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[The Master's programme in International and European Law is aimed at students who are planning a career in international law or European law. ]]></programSummary><programSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Master's programme in International and European Law is aimed at students who are planning a career in international law or European law. ]]></programSummary><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Europa]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[internationalisering]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[rechten]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[wetgeving]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[internationaal recht]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[conflicten]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[criminaliteit]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[internationale samenwerking]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[juridisch]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[publiekrecht]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[strafrecht]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[terrorisme]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Europe]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[internationalisation]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[law]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[legislation]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[international law]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[conflict]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[crime]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[international cooperation]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[judiciary]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[public law]]></search